<TITLE> Don't make people suffer in Ramadan: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 24 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has urged traders and businessmen not to make people suffer during the Ramadan, an aide said on Monday. The prime minister launched the appeal from a regular cabinet meeting, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters at a news briefing organised at the information directorate. "The prime minister also said it was the businessmen's moral responsibility to do what she had urged them to during the holy month." The meeting adopted a number of decisions including relocation of Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority head office to Narayanganj. b
